variables.value: Oh, that kit... You're from <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>, right?
<FST:KAMEO>'s always running from his problems...\nit's kinda his thing.
That staff guy was super nice.\nHelped me sort out some gear and even came with me to practice...
Maybe that's the guy you're after?\nHe rushed off just now.
What I like to eat while exercising?
Rice balls, for sure.\nThe perfect snack to curb post-workout hunger pangs.
The new guy, <FUL:YAMADA>.\nHe's a blond kid with glasses, should be wearing a staff uniform.
Thanks for finding <FUL:YAMADA>.\nWith him around, we can handle anything.
Now that you mention it...\nthe guy who helped clean earlier... Never seen him before.
Might've been <FUL:YAMADA>. He found a lost kid while cleaning\nand took 'em to the management center.
<FUL:YAMADA>...? Oh, the new guy! Yeah, he brought a lost kid here.
Huh? Looks like he's already gone...
Thanks for finding the ball. You've got this! Keep it up!
Huh, your hair looks just like that shadowy figure\nI saw Thursday night.
You weren't out that night? Then who—or what—was that shadow?!
Could you ask three atheletes\nwhat they feel like eating during workouts?
To enjoy the food while eating healthy...\nAnd here I thought it was a great concept...
What I crave when I'm exercising?
I think of drinks more than food.\nSports drink slushies hit the spot.
What I want to have during a workout? Protein, of course!
I love working out.\nJust imagining my muscles growing makes it taste even better!
The staff warned me not to pester players out of the blue.\nBut once I get a chance, I'll come back for that interview!
The Skycraft's good to go anytime!\nWe keep it in tip-top shape, so no worries.
Still training this late? Gotta say, I'm impressed.\nDon't worry! The Skycraft's still up and running.
Hey, you're from <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>, right? Congrats on winning\nyour first match! Hop on anytime you need a ride back to school.
The Skycraft might be small, but it fits more folks than you'd think!
You <MNT:NAGUMOHARA> folks actually beat Royal Academy!\nThat's wild! Need a ride today too? Gotta prep for the big game, huh.
Hop on now if you\nstill need a lift!
Heading back to <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>?\nA bit of hometown air might help clear your head.
Let me know\nif you need anything!
How are you liking the Football Gardens?\nDinner's already being prepared at the cottage. Hope you're hungry!
This is the management center.\nFeel free to ask if you need any gear or supplies!
And if you need\nanything, just ask!
It's about the time of day you might want a little break.\nThere are some nice benches in the plaza!
Finally, it's that time\nof year again!
I wonder who's\ngonna shine this time...
I take behind-the-scenes shots for the "Behind the Heroes"\nseries on the official socials. Gets a great response every year.
The photos get turned into cards after the tourney.\nA lot of fans look forward to them, so I give it my all.
You can even see it\nin how they move.
I can't stop taking\ntons of photos!
I post practice shots too! It's fun seeing how each school\ngets different comments, like “Alpine is so chill!”
Alpine's players shine with pure joy, while Noble Insight's\ngot that magnetic, can't-look-away vibe.
I'm just as hyped\nas the fans!
I got a few shots of your team too!\nThere's a ton of support out there for you.
There's something special about the mood before the final.\nWe're really looking forward to seeing how it plays out.
So this is <FUL:ENDO>'s statue... It really looks different in person.\nThere's this quiet strength that's hard to explain.
Our captain, <FLC:FUTATSUMIYA>, is seriously dedicated.\nI think someone like him deserves a statue too.
Twenty-five years ago, Raimon came out of nowhere and made history.\nThat unpredictability there is the magic of football.
Even after losing, teams can still use the Football Gardens.\nOur school's sticking around to keep training till the end.
Raimon's strength wasn't built overnight... but <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>\nhas this momentum that feels like it could change everything.
The cottages are surrounded by nature on purpose.\nHelps ease the tension before matches, or so I've heard.
AI's already mapped out the most efficient training plan.\nAll that's left is to follow it.
We'll break down why we lost to Royal later. Manager <LST:SOYOGI>'s\nanalysis is on another level.
Finals prep going okay?\nIf you need a sparring partner, try hitting up AI Academy.
We've gotta keep everything spotless so the players can do their best!\nEveryone on staff here really loves youth football.
One of the Lawcrest kids thanked me for cleaning earlier.\nMade me feel like I'd won an award or something!
Every time I polish <LST:ENDO>'s statue, I think back to 25 years ago.\nIt was a brilliant underdog run, just like the one <MNT:NAGUMOHARA>'s on now!
Can't help but keep\nwatching, gotta know...
So this is the mecca\nof football...!
Not a single break\nin their formation.
Let's take a quick break\nin the plaza.
It's huge, and there\nare tons of people...
Could be a nice\nchange of pace.
The view was beautiful,\ndon't you think?
<MNT:NAGUMOHARA> can use the pitch freely until the finals!\nBut heading back to your home turf might not be a bad idea.
All the way from Kyushu, huh?\nJust making it here ought to be a good memory for you.
A no-name school that can't even use Keshin?\nThat's no threat to us. Still... do your best, I guess.
I can't believe it still\neludes me...
Not a single shell out here meets my high standards!\nHow is that even possible with a beach this size?!
Whoa! This is perfection! A flawless specimen! Merci beaucoup!
